Artix installation instructions

* loadkeys uk
* partition disks
* mkfs.ext4 -L ROOT /dev/sda2
* mkfs.fat -F 32 /dev/sda1
* fatlabel /dev/sda1 BOOT
* mount /dev/disk/by-label/ROOT /mnt
* mkdir /mnt/boot
* mount /dev/disk/by-label/BOOT /mnt/boot
* basestrap /mnt base base-devel openrc linux linux-firmware
* fstabgen -L /mnt >> /mnt/etc/fstab
* artool-chroot /mnt

In new environment
* ln -sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/London /etc/localtime
* hwclock --systohc
* edit /etc/locale.gen, uncomment out the one you want
* locale-gen
* passwd to set root password
* set /etc/hostname
* /etc/hosts add 127.0.0.1 localhost / ::1 localhost / 127.0.1.1 kenny-linux.localdomain kenny-linux
* install + enable networkmanager (rc-update add network-manager)
* install grub efibootmgr
* grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot --bootloader-id=GRUB
* grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
* exit

Back in live environment
* umount -R /mnt
* reboot
* tada
